    <p>{`The first step is to setup the domain to the nameserver. You have multiple options. You can use Namecheap to handle it or to user Azure. Namecheap have a BasicDNS, a WebHosting DNS and a Custom DNS. Normally, if you are adding a domain to an existing VPS (not from NameCheap), you select "Custom DNS" and set the nameserver to the one provided by the VPS merchant during the setup of your account. For azure, it's the same thing. In NameCheap, go in the "Domain List", click "Manage" next to the domain you want to modify. Under the first tab, named "Domain" change the Custom DNS name for Azure ones.`}</p>
